Male last ventrite emarginated. Gonoforceps slender in ventral view (

Fig. 13 
A

), with lobes very long, in lateral view cylindrical and lobes short (
Fig. 13B
); gonocoxal plate only quite widened; aedeagus (
Fig. 13B
) with two apical hooks, similarly inclined and sharped, prossimal one longer.

[

Hycleus subarcuatefasciatus
(
Pic, 1941
)

]

Other records :
Namibia
( Bologna 2000a ;
Pitzalis et al. 2014
).

Other records
: Damaraland (

Kaszab 1955b, as ab. 
zumpti

); Namib Sand Sea desert (
Seel, 2012
); 

Namibia
(
Bologna 2000a
)

; SW Afrika (

Kaszab 1955b, as ab. 
welwitschiacola

). The species was described from “Cafrérie” (
Marseul 1872
), but probably this is a generic definition of southern Africa. 
Schultze (1908)
recorded the species also from Kalahari, but probably this record is erroneous.
